**~-~-The topic is defined by the phrase following the colon – the USFG is the agent of the resolution, not the individual debaters**

**Webster’s** Guide to Grammar and Writing – **2k**

[[http:~~/~~/ccc.commnet.edu/grammar/marks/colon.htm&amp;#62;&amp;#62;url:http://ccc.commnet.edu/grammar/marks/colon.htm]]

f

Use of a colon before a list or an explanation that is preceded by a clause that can stand by itself. Think of the colon as a gate, inviting one to go on… If the introductory phrase preceding the colon ispres very brief and the clause following the colon represents the real business of the sentence, begin the clause after the colon with a capital letter.

